raw_data.title: ERM Software Integrator
raw_data.description: Analyzes functional business requirements and design specifications for functional activities. Provide identification and fixes for problems within existing systems and enhancement of existing systems and participates in analysis, design and new construction of next generation IT systems. Develops integrated system test requirement, strategies, devices and systems. Responsible for understanding the needs of the customers and the realities of commercially available IT products, and creating requirements that will allow implementation by the architecture and engineering team and COTS products. Must possess systems engineering experience in one or more areas including telecommunications concepts, computer languages, operating systems, database/DBMS and middleware. The Systems Integrator for ERM much have expertise with integrating Content Management Systems such as M365 SharePoint on-Prem/Online with an Electronic Records Management COTS product such as Gimmal, Collabspace, Active Nav, Feith just to name a few both on-prem and SaaS. The Software Integrator must be familiar with multiple technology Platforms and is able to recommend a migration path of structure and unstructured data between the Content Management Systems and the ERM Products in order to ensure compliance with the NARA mandates. The Software Integrator must possess certifications for the installation and implementation of content management systems, and must be certified in installing, configuring and integrating the ERM COTS products. ERM Product Certification may be waived in the place of 1 year of product experience.

raw_data.title: Records Management (RM) /Subject Matter Expert (SME)
raw_data.description: Develop and/or manage records programs that provide support to the Government and has experience with file plans in accordance with NARA. Other examples of specialized experience include editing, drafting, and writing file plans, performing a wide variety of analytical studies and projects related to records management improvement, records management productivity improvement, records management controls, and long-range records planning including developing guidance on techniques for records management and records methods improvement, analyzing and advising on proposed reorganizations or realignment of functions in the context of handling records, and developing manuals and directives covering varying aspects of records operations. Review, synthesize and prepare highly technical, sensitive and complex documents, white papers, briefing materials, management directives and correspondence. Expert working knowledge of proper record-keeping, organization, handling, storage, retrieval, and proper  destruction of records for the organization in adherence to internal policies and external requirements. Expert knowledge of deployment of enterprise wide RM solutions with various products for managing paper, electronic and email records using knowledge management principles. Conduct assessment of various products and solutions and how they apply to the organization

raw_data.title: ERM Reports Analyst & Designer
raw_data.description: Generates reports from the ERM System, reports could be canned reports and already exist in the ERM System, or they could be reports that have to be custom built using report design products that connect and integrate with the ERM System. Examples of reports are: Destruction Certificates, report for records due for destruction that require approval, cutoff reports, vital records reports, duplicate records reports, sensitive data and CUI data reports just to name a few. The Report Analyst also understands the data and is able to tailor reports based on user needs, and train users on generating pre-built reports and how to read their data so they can make informed decisions about their records. The report analyst has extensive analytical and communication skills to communicate with the users on their structured and unstructured data in order to design reports specific to the mission of the organization, and trains the users on report features of the ERM Product.

raw_data.title: ERM Subject Matter Expert
raw_data.description: Provides extremely high?level ERM Specialized subject matter expertise for work described in the task. Responsible for creating a comprehensive architecture for the ERM Solution and providing strategic direction throughout the systems integration and implementation process of the ERM Solution. Ensures that the new solution fits into the existing enterprise architecture from technical, business, user, and Programmatic and legal requirements. Acts as the Solution Architect and technical SME for ERM Assessment projects and works alongside the RM SME who’s more specialized in RM Policy and Programs. Evaluates the data architecture, the information and business architecture and governance, and provides a technical approach and roadmap for implementing ERM tailored to the organization and the mission. Conducts proof of concept of the proposed solution by prototyping one business process, then recommending a way forward. Cooperates with all teams involved in the ERM Implementation and needs to know how every product and service works in the architecture. Oversees the successful delivery and quality of the end product to the end users, and provides Enterprise Governance Support and subject matter expertise of the newly implemented ERM System. Offers advanced technical or practical knowledge of highly specialized tasks. Prepares and organizes reports identifying results of study and evaluation. Makes recommendations on appropriate actions. Applies principles, methods, and knowledge of functional areas of expertise to task requirements. Provides advice and consultation on problems, which require extensive knowledge of subject matter. Prepares and delivers presentations and briefings as required by task order. May serve as task leader responsible for ensuring the quality and timeliness of services delivered. Must possess experience in Information Technology (IT) engagements and consulting on enterprise architecture, business process transformation and Enterprise Application Integration (EAI) in the Federal Government. Must have ERM Product Training and Certifications.
